<div
	layout="row"
    ng-show="active == 'profile'">
              
	<form name="profileForm">        
		<md-input-container  class="md-block" flex-gt-xs >
			<label>Name</label>
			<input ng-model="profile.name" md-maxlength="25" name="name" required md-asterisk>
			<div ng-messages="profileForm.name.$error">
				<div ng-message="required">Du musst einen Namen haben</div>
			</div>
		</md-input-container>
		<md-input-container  class="md-block" flex-gt-xs>
			<label>Image</label>
			<input ng-model="profile.imageUrl" md-maxlength="50">
		</md-input-container>
		<md-input-container  class="md-block" flex-gt-xs>
			<label>Twitter Name</label>
			<input ng-model="profile.twitterName" md-maxlength="25">
		</md-input-container>
		<md-input-container  class="md-block" flex-gt-xs>
			<label>Game Tag</label>
			<input ng-model="profile.hashTag" md-maxlength="3" name="tag" required md-asterisk>
			<div ng-messages="profileForm.tag.$error">
					<div ng-message="required">Du musst einen Tag haben</div>
				</div>
		</md-input-container>
	</form>
		
</div>
<div
	layout="row"
    ng-show="active == 'profile'">
    Änderungen werden ggf erst beim erneutem Login für dich sichtbar sein.<br>
	<md-button ng-disabled="profileForm.$invalid"  ng-click="submitProfile()">speichern</md-button>
</div>
